The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, March 08, 2004 				 Two-day meet on insurance
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, March 7: The insurance community is organising a high-level meeting to discuss the challenges ahead for the fairly new industry in developing countries.																								General Insurance Corporation (GIC), the national reinsurer, will be the host to the 14th Insurance Congress of Developing Countries (ICDC), a biennial event scheduled to take place next week. This is the second time that India is hosting the event  the first was in 1992.																								The insurance congress is being organised in association with the Insurance Regulatory Development Authority (IRDA).																								Various insurance and reinsurance firms and intermediaries, regulatory bodies, actuaries, risk management and other service providers will be participating in this two-day meet.																								While the theme of the programme is towards a more dynamic and responsive insurance environment, P. B. Ramanujam, managing director of GIC, said, The conference will see various developing countries working in harmony to discuss issues of common relevance and prepare for the challenges ahead. 
